#)Enum
is a special data type in Java that represents a fixed set of constants
like days of the week, directions, or statuses.

â€œAn enum in Java is a special class that defines a group of constants.
Itâ€™s type-safe, more readable than static final variables, and can include fields, methods, and constructors.â€


--------------------------------------------------------------------------
enum Day {
    SUNDAY, MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY, SATURDAY
}

public class EnumExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Day today = Day.MONDAY;

        switch (today) {
            case MONDAY:
                System.out.println("Start of the week!");
                break;
            case FRIDAY:
                System.out.println("Weekend is near!");
                break;
            default:
                System.out.println("Midweek day!");
        }
    }
}

