What are Variable Arguments (Varargs) in Java?

Variable Arguments (varargs) allow you to pass zero or more arguments of the same type to a method without explicitly creating an array



public class VarargsExample {
    static int sum(int... numbers) {
        int total = 0;
        for (int n : numbers) {
            total += n;
        }
        return total;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(sum());          // 0 â†’ zero arguments
        System.out.println(sum(5));         // 5 â†’ one argument
        System.out.println(sum(1, 2, 3, 4)); // 10 â†’ multiple arguments
    }
}
