#)What is assert in Java?
assert is a statement used for debugging purposes.
It tests a boolean condition; if the condition is false, it throws an AssertionError.
Mainly used to check assumptions in the code during development.

public class AssertExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int age = 15;
        assert age >= 18 : "Age must be 18 or older"; // Throws AssertionError if false
        System.out.println("Age is valid");
    }
}


